---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <div class="flex flex-col">
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 mb-6">
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-1">
        <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold">Privacy Policy for SproutJourney</h1>
        <p class="text-sm">
          Last Updated: <span class="font-bold">22 September 2024</span>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          Welcome to SproutJourney, an AI-powered educational platform tailored
          for children aged 6-12. We take privacy seriously and are committed to
          complying with the <span class="regulation"
            >General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)</span
          >, the <span class="regulation"
            >California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA)</span
          >, and other applicable privacy regulations. This Privacy Policy
          outlines how we collect, use, and protect personal data, ensuring
          transparency and safeguarding your rights.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>2. Data We Collect</h2>
        <p>
          We collect the following personal data to improve the educational
          experience:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <span class="data-type">Personal Identification Data:</span> Name, email
            address.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="data-type">Performance Data:</span> Learning progress, activity
            logs, preferences.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="data-type">Device Information:</span> IP address, device
            type, and usage data (for internal analytics).
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>3. Purpose of Data Collection</h2>
        <p>We collect and process this data to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Personalize learning experiences tailored to each child's unique
            needs.
          </li>
          <li>
            Track and report user performance to authorized parents or
            educational institutions.
          </li>
          <li>
            Improve the overall functionality of the platform based on user data
            and analytics.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This data will not be used for marketing purposes or shared with any
          third-party entities for commercial purposes.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>4. Data Sharing</h2>
        <p>
          We do not share user data with third parties, except in the following
          limited circumstances:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <span class="entity">Parents/Guardians:</span> Have access to their child's
            learning data and progress reports.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="entity">Educational Institutions:</span> If a child is using
            SproutJourney under the supervision of an institution, their progress
            may be shared with authorized personnel within the institution.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="entity">Payment Platforms:</span> Payments for individual
            users are processed through platforms like Google Play or equivalent,
            managed by the parent or guardian.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not share data with advertisers or third-party analytics
          providers, ensuring the utmost protection of your child's privacy.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>5. User Rights and Consent</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <span class="right">Access and Correction:</span> Parents, guardians,
            or educational institutions can access and correct the child's personal
            data through their accounts. Children do not have direct access to modify
            their own data.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="right">Data Deletion:</span> You can request deletion of
            personal data at any time by contacting us at <span class="email"
              >info@sproutjourney.in</span
            >. Data will be deleted within a reasonable timeframe unless
            required to be retained for legal obligations.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="right">Consent:</span> Consent is obtained by users accepting
            our Terms and Conditions. By using SproutJourney, you agree to this Privacy
            Policy.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          We retain personal data for as long as a user is active on the
          platform. After termination of services, we archive user data for a
          period of 1-2 years to comply with legal obligations and to provide
          assistance if users return. After this period, the data will be
          permanently deleted.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>7. Data Security</h2>
        <p>
          We implement stringent organizational and technical measures to
          protect personal data. Our platform uses secure databases like
          Supabase, which comply with GDPR and CCPA standards. However, no
          online platform can guarantee 100% security, and we encourage users to
          practice good security habits.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          As a platform for children, we comply with the <span
            class="regulation"
            >Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA)</span
          > and GDPR's specific provisions regarding minors. We do not knowingly
          collect data from children without parental consent. If we learn that a
          child under 13 has provided personal data without parental consent, we
          will promptly delete such information.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>9. Updates to this Policy</h2>
        <p>
          This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically to reflect changes in
          legal requirements or our data practices. We will notify you of any
          significant changes by posting an updated policy on this page and
          sending an email notification to registered users.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>10. Contact Information</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy or
          your data rights, please contact us at:
        </p>
        <p>Email: <span class="email">info@sproutjourney.in</span></p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-1">
        <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold">
          Terms and Conditions for SproutJourney
        </h1>
        <p class="text-sm">
          Last Updated: <span class="font-bold">22 September 2024</span>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms and Conditions govern your use of SproutJourney (the
          "Platform"). By accessing or using the Platform, you agree to abide by
          these terms, including our Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with
          any part of these terms, you should refrain from using the Platform.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>2. User Eligibility</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            SproutJourney is designed for use by children aged 6-12. Children
            may only use the Platform with the consent and supervision of a
            parent, guardian, or educational institution.
          </li>
          <li>
            Parents and guardians are responsible for managing the child's
            account and ensuring compliance with these terms.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>3. Prohibited Conduct</h2>
        <p>The following behaviors are strictly prohibited:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Using offensive or inappropriate language, including attempting to
            trick the AI into generating such content.
          </li>
          <li>
            Manipulating or cheating the system for personal gain or to disrupt
            the learning experience for others.
          </li>
          <li>
            Engaging in any activity that could harm the platform, such as
            hacking or introducing malware.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to suspend or terminate any account involved in
          such activities.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>4. Payments and Subscriptions</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <span class="subscription-type">Individual Subscriptions:</span> For
            individual users, payments are processed through platforms such as Google
            Play or similar services. Payments will be on a recurring basis, and
            parents/guardians are responsible for managing these payments.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="subscription-type">Institutional Subscriptions:</span> For
            educational institutions, payment structures may vary based on agreements
            with SproutJourney. Children will not be involved in these transactions.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="subscription-action">Cancellation:</span> You may cancel
            your subscription by submitting a cancellation request through our platform.
            Upon cancellation, access to the platform will be terminated at the end
            of the current billing cycle.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>5. Content Ownership</h2>
        <p>
          All content on SproutJourney, including lessons, animations, and
          user-generated content, remains the property of SproutJourney. Users
          are granted a limited, non-exclusive license to use the platform's
          content during their subscription.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>6. Data and Privacy</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Personal data collected during platform usage is processed in
            compliance with our Privacy Policy. We use this data solely for
            internal purposes, such as improving the learning experience and
            tracking progress.
          </li>
          <li>
            Parents and educational institutions have access to view and manage
            the child's data. Children do not have direct control over their
            data.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>7. Account Termination</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            We reserve the right to terminate or suspend accounts that violate
            these Terms and Conditions or attempt to manipulate or misuse the
            platform.
          </li>
          <li>
            Upon termination, access to all content and data associated with the
            account may be removed or archived, as outlined in our Privacy
            Policy.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>8. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
        <p>
          SproutJourney strives to provide a high-quality and effective learning
          experience, but we do not guarantee that the platform will always be
          available, error-free, or meet specific learning outcomes. All
          services are provided "as is," and we disclaim any warranties to the
          maximum extent permitted by law.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the fullest extent permitted by law, SproutJourney shall not be
          liable for any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising
          from the use of the platform, including but not limited to loss of
          data, interruptions, or errors in service.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>10. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms and Conditions are governed by and construed in accordance
          with the laws of <span class="jurisdiction">[Your Jurisdiction]</span
          >, without regard to its conflict of law principles. Any disputes
          arising under these terms will be resolved in the courts of <span
            class="jurisdiction">[Your Jurisdiction]</span
          >.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>11. Modifications to Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to modify these Terms and Conditions at any time.
          Significant changes will be communicated to users via email or through
          a notification on the platform. Continued use of the platform after
          such changes will constitute acceptance of the revised terms.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>12. Contact Information</h2>
        <p>
          For any questions or concerns regarding these Terms and Conditions,
          please contact us at:
        </p>
        <p>Email: <span class="email">info@sproutjourney.in</span></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  h2 {
    font-size: large;
    font-weight: bold;
  }
</style>
